Interface ITagManagerBackEnd

All Known Implementing Classes:
TagManagerBackEnd
public interface ITagManagerBackEnd

Interface for the TagManagerBackEnd Provides functionality for handling public and community tags. The methods provided will be available through web service calls. Adapted for Astra

Version:
0.3
Author:
Christian Laverton, modified by David Rozas & Alfredo Perez

addTag

boolean addTag(java.lang.String name,
               java.lang.String appId,
               java.lang.String userId)
Creates a new tag. This method is overloaded, when it is invoked with these parameters (no community) a public tag is created Adapted for Astra.

Parameters:
name - Tag name
appId - Application identifier
userId - User identifier
Returns:
True if the operation was successful, false otherwise.

getTags

java.lang.String[] getTags(java.lang.String appId,
                           int limit)
Finds and returns all tags for the given application. This method is overloaded, when it is invoked with these parameters (no community) the public tags are retrieved. The tags returned are unique (if many users chose the same name, it will only appears once) and it is sorted by popularity (number of occurrences).

Parameters:
appId - Application identifier
limit - Limit on number of results returned. If <=0, then all the results are returned
Returns:
List of public tags resulting from query, empty array if there no tags for it, or null if there was any problem with the DB.

getTagsByCommunity

java.lang.String[] getTagsByCommunity(java.lang.String appId,
                                      int limit,
                                      java.lang.String communityId)
Finds and returns all tags for the given application and community. The tags returned are unique (if many users chose the same name, it will only appears once) and it is sorted by popularity (number of occurrences).

Parameters:
appId - Application identifier
limit - Limit on number of results returned. If <=0, then all the results are returned
communityId - Community identifier
Returns:
List of tags which belong to that community resulting from query, empty array if there no tags for it, or null if there was any problem with the DB.

getTagsByApplication

java.lang.String[] getTagsByApplication(java.lang.String appId,
                                        java.lang.String userId,
                                        int limit)
Finds and returns all tags for the given application which are public or are from a community where the user is part of. The tags returned are unique (if many users chose the same name, it will only appears once) and it is sorted by popularity (number of occurrences).

Parameters:
appId - Application identifier
userId - User identifier
limit - Limit on number of results returned. If <=0, then all the results are returned
Returns:
List of tags which belong to that community resulting from query, empty array if there no tags for it, or null if there was any problem with the DB.
